[2026-01-17 12:16:56] gh pr create --title "fix(security): prevent command injection in Android stage display" --body "$(cat <<'EOF'
## Summary

- **Command injection prevention**: Added strict input validation for `host` (alphanumeric, dots, hyphens only) and `launch_component` (package/activity format) fields
- **ADB timeout protection**: Added 10-second timeout for all ADB commands to prevent indefinite hangs

## Security Details

The Android stage display feature executes ADB shell commands using user-provided `host` and `launch_component` values. Without validation, an attacker could inject shell metacharacters (`;`, `|`, `$()`, etc.) to execute arbitrary commands.

**Mitigations applied:**
1. Host validation: Only allows `[a-zA-Z0-9.-]` characters
2. Component validation: Only allows `[a-zA-Z0-9._/]` characters and requires `/` separator
3. Command timeout: Prevents resource exhaustion from hanging connections

## Test plan

- [x] Build passes
- [x] All tests pass
- [x] Clippy clean

🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)
EOF
)"
